name: Prophecy and Magic for Beginners: Poetry Reading
description:
prophecy and magic for beginners

to start: a basic interpretation to confirm your existing fears or hopes, the unexpressed sort — 
the kitchen thoughts that hover over eggs and 
black coffee 
so that three swords become a loss, upcoming 
(though perhaps you have turned your card 
in just such a way 
that you have cleverly averted disaster) 

so too, that any trinkets offering protection from 
          unexpected bills 
          phone calls at 4 a.m. 
          rotten produce, noticed too late 
have a strange charm about them, and ride 
alongside your errands and daily commute 

the Pythia can inhale vapors of ethylene gas 
and ruin your entire Wednesday — 
she is neatly avoided by turning instead to 
augury 
and detecting in the flight patterns of local birds 
the way to a promotion or large sum of money 

(so I am told)
